---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PostCardFeatured from '~/components/PostCardFeatured.astro';
import SidebarPostLink from '~/components/SidebarPostLink.astro';
import TinkeringStrip from '~/components/TinkeringStrip.astro';
import CloveHitch from '~/components/CloveHitch.astro';
import { getAllPostsSorted } from '~/lib/tags';

const allPosts = await getAllPostsSorted();
const featuredPosts = allPosts.filter((p) => p.data.featured);
const heroPost = featuredPosts[0] ?? allPosts[0];
const sidebarPosts = featuredPosts.length > 0
  ? featuredPosts.slice(1, 6)
  : allPosts.slice(1, 6);

const principles = [
  {
    n: '01',
    body:
      'Designs should be simple. Interactions within design should be ridiculously simple. A decade of design systems taught me that complexity is almost always a sign that someone upstream didn’t make a decision.',
  },
  {
    n: '02',
    body:
      'Figma is the right place to start. It’s almost never the long-term source of truth. The moment you’re building a real design system, the npm package starts pulling ahead — and knowing when to go back to Figma to reconcile, versus when to keep building forward, is the judgment most teams never develop.',
  },
  {
    n: '03',
    body:
      'AI in design is a knowledge problem before it’s a prompt problem. Most teams skip straight to prompting, then wonder why the output sounds like no one who works there.',
  },
  {
    n: '04',
    body:
      'The napkin sketch is the spec. Figma is a translation, code is a translation, and the meeting where someone asks “but what did you mean by this?” is what happens when the intent didn’t survive the trip.',
  },
  {
    n: '05',
    body:
      'Simple, yet strong. Knots and components work the same way — they hold until the requirements change, and then you see what you actually built.',
  },
];

const workshopChips = [
  'Bearpaw',
  'Kerchunk',
  'Meshtastic KC',
  'Amateur radio',
  'Music experiments',
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Jeremy Fuksa — The Cocktail Napkin"
  description="Jeremy Fuksa — thirty years of design, plus the work in progress: design systems, AI design pipelines, and what gets sketched before any of it becomes real."
>
  <TinkeringStrip />

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <h1 class="hero-h1">The cocktail napkin is older than design.</h1>
      <p class="hero-thesis">It’s where the idea is allowed to be wrong — before the deck, the Figma file, the Jira ticket.</p>
      <p class="hero-body">Mine used to be a Moleskine. Then a whiteboard. Lately it’s been a Claude chat session open in Plan Mode.</p>
      <p class="hero-cta-row">
        <a href="/work/" class="hero-cta">See the work</a>
        <span class="hero-cta-sep" aria-hidden="true">&middot;</span>
        <span class="hero-cta-or">or</span>
        <span class="hero-cta-sep" aria-hidden="true">&middot;</span>
        <a href="/writing/" class="hero-cta">Read the writing</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="principles" aria-label="Principles">
    <div class="principles-inner">
      <div class="principles-grid">
        <ol class="principles-list">
          {principles.map((p) => (
            <li class="principle">
              <span class="principle-number">{p.n}</span>
              <p class="principle-body">{p.body}</p>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ol>
        <div class="principles-figure">
          <CloveHitch />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="featured-work" aria-label="Featured work">
    <div class="featured-work-inner">
      <div class="featured-work-grid">
        <a href="/work/domain-foundation/" class="featured-work-card">
          <span class="featured-work-label">Methodology</span>
          <h2 class="featured-work-title">Domain Foundation</h2>
          <p class="featured-work-body">Encoding institutional design expertise as layered, machine-readable knowledge an AI can reason with. Because default models produce default output.</p>
          <span class="featured-work-link">Read the case study &rarr;</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/work/moonbird/" class="featured-work-card">
          <span class="featured-work-label">Case study</span>
          <h2 class="featured-work-title">Moonbird</h2>
          <p class="featured-work-body">A year building a RAG pipeline &mdash; vector database, MCP server, Figma Make integration &mdash; to generate design-system-aligned UI inside Oracle Health. The research that became Domain Foundation.</p>
          <span class="featured-work-link">Read the case study &rarr;</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/work/terra-design-system/" class="featured-work-card">
          <span class="featured-work-label">Case study</span>
          <h2 class="featured-work-title">Terra Design System</h2>
          <p class="featured-work-body">Open-source React component library at Cerner. 80+ components, 200+ icons, WCAG 2.1 AA, Apache 2.0. UX designer working directly in the React codebase alongside engineering.</p>
          <span class="featured-work-link">Read the case study &rarr;</span>
        </a>
      </div>
      <a href="/work/" class="featured-work-all">See all work &rarr;</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="home-writing-section" aria-labelledby="home-writing-heading">
    <div class="home-writing-inner">
      <h2 class="home-writing-heading" id="home-writing-heading">A journal of unbridled creativity</h2>
      <div class="home-writing-grid">
        <main>
          {heroPost && <PostCardFeatured entry={heroPost} />}
        </main>
        <aside class="sidebar">
          <span class="section-title">Previous</span>
          <nav class="sidebar-posts">
            {sidebarPosts.map((entry) => <SidebarPostLink entry={entry} />)}
            <a href="/writing/" class="sidebar-posts-all">All posts &rarr;</a>
          </nav>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="workshop-bridge" aria-labelledby="workshop-bridge-heading">
    <div class="workshop-bridge-inner">
      <span class="workshop-bridge-eyebrow">A room next to this one</span>
      <h2 class="workshop-bridge-headline" id="workshop-bridge-heading">The Workshop.</h2>
      <div class="workshop-bridge-body">
        <p>Bear Paw is a control system for Uniden scanners. Kerchunk is a Pi Zero 2W and a stick SDR I&rsquo;m trying to get into something pocket-sized. I&rsquo;ve been running a Meshtastic mesh network across Kansas City. I spent three months trying to break my Apple Music algorithm on purpose.</p>
        <p>The Workshop is where I keep all of this. Hiring managers can skip it. Designers who keep reading will probably stay.</p>
      </div>
      <ul class="workshop-bridge-chips" aria-label="Workshop topics">
        {workshopChips.map((chip) => (
          <li><a href="/workshop/" class="workshop-chip">{chip}</a></li>
        ))}
        <li><a href="/workshop/" class="workshop-chip workshop-chip-more">+ more</a></li>
      </ul>
      <a href="/workshop/" class="workshop-bridge-cta">Enter the Workshop &rarr;</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
